cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS

This paper deals with database problems related to ontology-mediated querying and querying in the presence of constraints, which are both subfields of database theory (cs.DB). The use of guarded and frontier-guarded TGDs and UCQs as the actual queries suggests a connection to logic and knowledge representation (cs.AI) and logic and verification (cs.LO). The focus on efficient query evaluation implies a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
